Commentary Text: Nehra to Uthappa, no run, Nehra wants the caught behind. And such has been the day that he finds it necessary to charge towards the umpire in doing so. They decide to take matters upstairs - with OUT being the soft signal. Okay here's what transpired.. Uthappa looks to swivel as he wants to deposit the leg-liner into the stands behind square. Was it off the bat? Or the pad? Whatever it was, the ball lobs high and Ojha is made to run in from behind in diving to collect. Looks clean. Mind you, we need conclusive evidence here in this case to determine that the ball hasn't kissed the bat or the glove. Very difficult to determine despite all the slow-mos we have in place. Oh surprise, surprise..the decision is overruled. Uthappa survives. Continues his luck ride

Commentary Text: Bhuvneshwar to Uthappa, no run. Oh my! Uthappa has nicked that off the bat face to the keeper. Big, big nick. Warner appeals, pleads, begs and he doesn't give up as yet. Walks to the umpire and has a word. Crikey! How big a moment is this? An outswinger, pitches on a good length and grazes the thick outside edge as Uthappa looks to guide. The only reason could be Bhuvi - who didn't appeal instantly and almost joined the chorus on seeing his team-mates celebrate. Everyone looks shell-shocked. There was a clear deflection and the numerous replays reveal the same. Binga reckons the only culprit is Bhuvi who didn't appeal after the nick which prompted the umpire to stay unfazed

Commentary Text: Bhuvneshwar to Narine, out Bowled!! The off-stump goes flying. Bhuvi has had a fantastic bowling record over KKR and it only gets better. It swings in the air, lands on the seam and shapes just enough to uproot Narine's off-pole. The slash-flash batsman had no clue about that one. By the time the ball dipped in, Narine opened himself up completely and embarassed himself. Narine b Bhuvneshwar 6(9) [4s-1]
